	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's some tips.<br><br>1. Be prepared to change the scenery. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   You may have to leave Crush Bone to find a place to solo. I'd actually rate CB as one of the worst places. Go to the young aviaks in Lake Rathtear. That's probably the best place for now. It's a long way away but if you want to solo that's the best place to be right now. When you outgrow those aviaks go to the beetles in North Karna, etc<br><br>2. Maximize your abjuration.<br>     Root is your best friend. Maximize this skill by medding to full and casting root on yourself (in a safe place) over and over again. Or use "Fade" in an enclosed area or safe zone to raise your skill every time you level.<br><br>3. Don't expect to solo forever<br>     Wizards are not meant to solo. They are best when able to sit in the background of a full group, keep mana there, and use it when things need to be put back into control.<br><br>Take care and a grain of salt with what is said. These are some tips based on my meager exp as a soloing wizard.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
